  "text": "# Kafka Streams Topology Build to Processor Node Chain\n\n## Overview\nThe Kafka Streams topology is built through a multi-stage process that transforms a high-level DSL specification into a physical processor topology with initialized processor nodes and state stores.\n\n## Build Chain Flow\n\n### Stage 1: StreamsBuilder.build() - High-Level DSL Entry Point\n**File:** `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/StreamsBuilder.java` (lines 583-597)\n\nThe public API entry point where users call `builder.build()` or `builder.build(Properties)`. This method:\n- Accepts optional Properties for topology optimization configuration\n- Delegates to `InternalStreamsBuilder.buildAndOptimizeTopology(props)` (line 595)\n- Returns a compiled `Topology` object\n\nKey implementation: Contains `internalStreamsBuilder` (InternalStreamsBuilder instance) and `internalTopologyBuilder` (InternalTopologyBuilder instance) that work together.\n\n### Stage 2: InternalStreamsBuilder.buildAndOptimizeTopology() - Graph Traversal\n**File:** `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/InternalStreamsBuilder.java` (lines 308-337)\n\nThe DSL builder that maintains a graph of nodes representing the topology:\n- Merges duplicate source nodes via `mergeDuplicateSourceNodes()`\n- Performs topology optimization via `optimizeTopology(props)`\n- Enables versioned semantics via `enableVersionedSemantics()`\n- Traverses the graph in priority order using a priority queue\n- Calls `writeToTopology(internalTopologyBuilder)` on each GraphNode (line 325)\n\nGraph nodes include:\n- **StateStoreNode** (graph/StateStoreNode.java): Calls `topologyBuilder.addStateStore(storeBuilder)` (line 35)\n- **ProcessorGraphNode** (graph/ProcessorGraphNode.java): Calls `processorParameters.addProcessorTo(topologyBuilder, parentNodeNames())` (line 52)\n- **StreamSourceNode** (graph/StreamSourceNode.java): Calls `topologyBuilder.addSource(...)` with deserializers and timestamp extractors (lines 76-88)\n- Other graph nodes for operators like map, filter, join, aggregate, etc.\n\n### Stage 3: InternalTopologyBuilder - Physical Topology Construction\n**File:** `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/InternalTopologyBuilder.java`\n\n#### addStateStore() Method (lines 602-627)\nRegisters a state store with the topology:\n- Receives a `StoreFactory` (wraps StoreBuilder)\n- Stores it in `stateFactories` map (line 617)\n- Connects the store to processor nodes via `connectProcessorAndStateStore()` (line 622)\n- Invalidates cached nodeGroups for recomputation\n\n#### buildTopology() Method (lines 963-973)\nEntry point for building the full processor topology:\n- Calls `nodeGroups()` to get all processor/source/sink node groupings\n- Removes global state node groups\n- Calls `build(allNodes)` to construct the actual ProcessorTopology\n\n#### build() Method (lines 1012-1060)\nThe core method that constructs ProcessorTopology:\n\n1. **Node Factory Instantiation (lines 1023-1050)**:\n   - Iterates through `nodeFactories` (LinkedHashMap in topological order)\n   - For each factory in the node group:\n     - **ProcessorNodeFactory**: Builds ProcessorNode via `factory.build()` (line 1025)\n     - **SourceNodeFactory**: Builds SourceNode via `factory.build()` (line 1025), then calls `buildSourceNode()` (lines 1097-1115)\n     - **SinkNodeFactory**: Builds SinkNode via `factory.build()` (line 1025), then calls `buildSinkNode()` (lines 1062-1087)\n\n2. **State Store Building (lines 1118-1151 in buildProcessorNode)**:\n   - For each state store name referenced by a processor:\n     - Retrieves the `StoreFactory` from `stateFactories` map (line 1131)\n     - Configures the store factory with topology configs (line 1144)\n     - **Builds the StateStore**: Calls `storeFactory.builder().build()` (line 1146)\n     - Registers the built store in `stateStoreMap` (line 1147)\n     - Handles changelog topics for logging-enabled stores (lines 1134-1142)\n\n3. **ProcessorTopology Creation (lines 1052-1059)**:\n   - Constructs new ProcessorTopology with:\n     - List of built ProcessorNodes\n     - Map of source nodes by topic\n     - Map of sink nodes by topic\n     - List of built StateStores\n     - List of global state stores\n     - Store-to-changelog topic mappings\n     - Repartition topics set\n     - Store reprocess-on-restore configurations\n\n### Stage 4: ProcessorTopology - Physical Topology Container\n**File:** `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/ProcessorTopology.java` (lines 49-77)\n\nImmutable container holding:\n- `processorNodes`: List of ProcessorNode instances ready for execution\n- `sourceNodesByTopic`: Map of source topics to SourceNode consumers\n- `sinksByTopic`: Map of sink topics to SinkNode producers\n- `stateStores`: List of initialized StateStore instances\n- `globalStateStores`: List of global state stores\n- `storeToChangelogTopic`: Mapping for changelog topics\n- `repartitionTopics`: Set of internal repartition topics\n\n### Stage 5: StreamTask Processor Node Initialization\n**File:** `streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/internals/StreamTask.java` (lines 1080-1091)\n\nWhen a task is created for execution:\n1. StreamTask receives the ProcessorTopology in its constructor (line 125)\n2. During task initialization, `initializeTopology()` is called (line 296)\n3. For each ProcessorNode in the topology (line 1083):\n   - Sets the current node in processor context (line 1084)\n   - Calls `node.init(processorContext, processingExceptionHandler)` (line 1086)\n   - This initializes the processor with its context, allowing it to:\n     - Access state stores\n     - Register punctuation schedules\n     - Initialize internal processor state\n\n## Key Data Flow\n\n1. **StreamsBuilder** defines topology via DSL methods (stream, table, map, filter, etc.)\n2. **Graph nodes** are created for each operation and stored in InternalStreamsBuilder's graph\n3. **Graph traversal** in buildAndOptimizeTopology calls writeToTopology on each node\n4. **InternalTopologyBuilder** accumulates NodeFactory instances representing processors, sources, and sinks\n5. **StoreFactory instances** are registered in stateFactories map via StateStoreNode.writeToTopology()\n6. **buildTopology()** triggers the build process\n7. **build()** method:\n   - Builds ProcessorNodes from NodeFactory.build()\n   - Builds StateStores from StoreFactory.builder().build()\n   - Builds SourceNodes and SinkNodes\n   - Constructs ProcessorTopology with all components\n8. **ProcessorTopology** is passed to StreamTask\n9. **StreamTask.initializeTopology()** initializes each ProcessorNode for execution\n\n## Store Builder Registration Pipeline\n\n1. User calls `StreamsBuilder.addStateStore(StoreBuilder)` or uses materialized operators\n2. `StreamsBuilder.addStateStore()` calls `internalStreamsBuilder.addStateStore(StoreBuilderWrapper.wrapStoreBuilder(builder))` (line 530)\n3. `InternalStreamsBuilder.addStateStore()` creates `StateStoreNode(builder)` and adds it to the graph (line 220)\n4. During buildAndOptimizeTopology, `StateStoreNode.writeToTopology(internalTopologyBuilder)` is called\n5. This calls `internalTopologyBuilder.addStateStore(storeBuilder)` (StateStoreNode line 35)\n6. `InternalTopologyBuilder.addStateStore()` stores the StoreFactory in the `stateFactories` map (line 617)\n7. During `build()`, when processing processor nodes that reference the store:\n   - The StoreFactory is retrieved from `stateFactories` (line 1131)\n   - `storeFactory.builder().build()` is called to create the actual StateStore instance (line 1146)\n   - The store is added to `stateStoreMap` (line 1147)\n   - The store is passed to ProcessorTopology constructor\n\n## Summary\nThe topology compilation follows a clear separation of concerns: The DSL layer (StreamsBuilder, InternalStreamsBuilder) manages the logical topology graph, the InternalTopologyBuilder layer constructs physical node factories and builds the actual ProcessorTopology with initialized stores, and finally the StreamTask layer initializes processor nodes for runtime execution. Store builders are registered early and built just-in-time when the ProcessorTopology is constructed, allowing for proper configuration and integration with changelog topics."
